General information
===================

Libvoikko is a library for free natural language processing.
The core library is written in Rust. The VFST backend provides
morphology-based analysis for Finnish.

Libvoikko provides spell checking, hyphenation, grammar checking and
morphological analysis for Finnish language.


License
=======

The core library is available under MPL 1.1 / GPL 2+ / LGPL 2.1+ tri-license.

 Backend        License
----------------------------------------------------------------
 VFST           MPL 1.1 / GPL 2+ / LGPL 2.1+


Features
========

 - Spell checking using compound word and derivation rule system.
 - Spelling suggestions tuned for common typing errors and OCR correction.
 - Hyphenation with compound-aware splitting based on morphological analysis.
 - Grammar checking and context-sensitive spell checking using paragraph
   based API.
 - String tokenizer and sentence splitter.
 - Morphological analyzer.
 - Available through JS/TS (WASM), Python, Java, C#, Common Lisp, and C APIs.

Documentation for the C API can be found in the header file rust/crates/voikko-ffi/include/voikko.h.


Build (Rust)
============

  cd rust
  cargo test --all-features      # 637 tests
  cargo clippy --all-features -- -D warnings

WASM build:

  cd rust
  cargo build --target wasm32-unknown-unknown --release -p voikko-wasm
  wasm-bindgen target/wasm32-unknown-unknown/release/voikko_wasm.wasm \
    --out-dir ../js/wasm --target web --typescript

FFI shared library:

  cd rust
  cargo build --release -p voikko-ffi
  # → target/release/libvoikko_ffi.{dylib,so,dll}


Dictionary files
================

For dictionary format 5 (Finnish VFST backend):

 Valid VFST dictionaries can be built from voikko-fi version 2.0 or later.
 The dictionary path should contain: {path}/5/mor-standard/{files}

 Required files:
   - mor.vfst      (morphological transducer, ~3.8MB)
   - autocorr.vfst (autocorrect transducer, ~11KB)
   - index.txt     (dictionary metadata)


